  <discussion>Rhodobryum ontariense is a common and characteristic species of the eastern deciduous forests, occurring as far south as Arkansas and Georgia, with disjunct populations in the mountains of west Texas, New Mexico, and southeastern Arizona. The species is not found in arctic tundra and is rare in the northern boreal forests.</discussion>
